            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            Google will rewrite your meta description if it determines the text doesn't accurately describe your page, contains keyword stuffing, or if another snippet of text from your content is a better match for the user's search query.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            How do mobile search previews differ from desktop search previews?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            Mobile search results have smaller screen widths, meaning titles and descriptions are truncated sooner than on desktop (often cutting off descriptions at 120 characters instead of 160). Emojis and site favicons are also displayed more prominently in mobile search feeds.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            What are rich snippets and how do they affect SERP previews?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            Rich snippets are search results that display extra visual details alongside the title and description, such as review stars, recipe cook times, or product prices. They are generated by search engines parsing structured schema data in your HTML.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            How does search click-through rate (CTR) impact organic rankings?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            A high Click-Through Rate (CTR) indicates to search engines that your page is a relevant, appealing answer to a query. Over time, search engines may adjust rankings to promote pages that receive higher-than-average click rates.
          </div>
        </details>
      
        <details class="bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline rounded-xl overflow-hidden shadow-lvl2 group">
          <summary class="px-6 py-4 cursor-pointer flex items-center justify-between font-sans font-semibold text-sm text-ink list-none hover:bg-canvas-soft transition-colors select-none">
            Can emojis be used in meta descriptions and titles?
            <svg class="w-4 h-4 text-mute shrink-0 transition-transform group-open:rotate-180" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg>
          </summary>
          <div class="px-6 pb-5 text-sm text-body font-sans leading-relaxed border-t border-hairline pt-4">
            Yes, you can use emojis, but search engines do not guarantee they will display. Emojis can increase visual prominence on a search page, but they should be used sparingly and make sense for the topic to avoid looking spammy.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Related Tools Section -->
    <section class="max-w-4xl pt-16 mt-20 border-t border-hairline" aria-label="Related Tools">
      <h3 class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-wider text-mute mb-8">Related Marketing Tools</h3>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 gap-4">
        <a href="/marketing/meta-tag-generator" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            Meta Tag Generator
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Generate meta tags with Google and social sharing snippet previews.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/marketing/utm-builder" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            UTM Link Builder
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Generate campaign links with tracking codes and presets.</p>
        </a>
        <a href="/marketing/email-subject-tester" class="group bg-canvas ring-1 ring-inset ring-hairline hover:border-hairline-strong rounded-xl p-5 shadow-lvl1 hover:shadow-lvl2 transition-all">
          <h4 class="text-sm font-bold text-ink font-sans group-hover:text-primary transition-colors flex items-center gap-2">
            Email Subject Line Tester
            <svg class="w-3.5 h-3.5 text-mute group-hover:text-primary group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-all" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" d="M9 5l7 7-7 7"/></svg>
          </h4>
          <p class="text-mute text-xs font-sans mt-1.5">Test clipping sizes and flags email spam words.</p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<script>
  // ============================================================
  // DOM Elements
  // ============================================================
  const titleInput = document.getElementById('serp-title') as HTMLInputElement;
  const descInput = document.getElementById('serp-desc') as HTMLTextAreaElement;
  const urlInput = document.getElementById('serp-url') as HTMLInputElement;

  const toggleRating = document.getElementById('toggle-rating') as HTMLInputElement;
  const ratingInputs = document.getElementById('rating-inputs') as HTMLDivElement;
  const numRating = document.getElementById('num-rating') as HTMLInputElement;
  const numReviews = document.getElementById('num-reviews') as HTMLInputElement;

  const toggleFaq = document.getElementById('toggle-faq') as HTMLInputElement;
  const faqInputs = document.getElementById('faq-inputs') as HTMLDivElement;
  const faqQ1Input = document.getElementById('faq-q1') as HTMLInputElement;
  const faqQ2Input = document.getElementById('faq-q2') as HTMLInputElement;

  const btnViewDesktop = document.getElementById('btn-view-desktop') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const btnViewMobile = document.getElementById('btn-view-mobile') as HTMLButtonElement;

  const serpCardContainer = document.getElementById('serp-card-container') as HTMLDivElement;
  const mockBreadcrumb = document.getElementById('mock-breadcrumb') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const mockTitle = document.getElementById('mock-title') as HTMLAnchorElement;
  const mockDesc = document.getElementById('mock-desc') as HTMLParagraphElement;
  
  const mockStarsLine = document.getElementById('mock-stars-line') as HTMLDivElement;
  const mockStarsVal = document.getElementById('mock-stars-val') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const mockStarsVotes = document.getElementById('mock-stars-votes') as HTMLSpanElement;

  const mockFaqLine = document.getElementById('mock-faq-line') as HTMLDivElement;
  const mockFaqQ1 = document.getElementById('mock-faq-q1') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const mockFaqQ2 = document.getElementById('mock-faq-q2') as HTMLSpanElement;

  const titlePixelsLbl = document.getElementById('title-pixels-lbl') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const barTitlePixels = document.getElementById('bar-title-pixels') as HTMLDivElement;
  const titleWarnTxt = document.getElementById('title-warn-txt') as HTMLDivElement;

  const descPixelsLbl = document.getElementById('desc-pixels-lbl') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const barDescPixels = document.getElementById('bar-desc-pixels') as HTMLDivElement;
  const descWarnTxt = document.getElementById('desc-warn-txt') as HTMLDivElement;

  // ============================================================
  // State
  // ============================================================
  let viewMode: 'desktop' | 'mobile' = 'desktop';

  // Canvas context for measuring text widths in proportional Arial
  const canvas = document.createElement('canvas');
  const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;

  const getPixelWidth = (text: string, fontSpec: string) => {
    ctx.font = fontSpec;
    return ctx.measureText(text).width;
  };

  // ============================================================
  // Functions
  // ============================================================
  const updateSERP = () => {
    const titleVal = titleInput.value;
    const descVal = descInput.value;
    const urlVal = urlInput.value;

    // 1. URL parsing to format Breadcrumbs mockup
    let breadcrumbText = "https://example.com";
    try {
      const u = new URL(urlVal.startsWith('http') ? urlVal : 'https://' + urlVal);
      const parts = u.pathname.split('/').filter(Boolean);
      breadcrumbText = u.origin + (parts.length > 0 ? ' &rsaquo; ' + parts.join(' &rsaquo; ') : '');
    } catch(e) {
      breadcrumbText = urlVal;
    }
    mockBreadcrumb.innerHTML = breadcrumbText;

    // 2. Measure actual pixel footprint (Title: 20px Arial bold, Desc: 14px Arial)
    const titleWidth = getPixelWidth(titleVal, 'bold 20px Arial');
    const descWidth = getPixelWidth(descVal, '14px Arial');

    // Title Limits (600px desktop)
    const titleLimit = 600;
    const titlePercent = Math.min(100, (titleWidth / titleLimit) * 100);
    titlePixelsLbl.textContent = `${Math.round(titleWidth)}px / ${titleLimit}px`;
    barTitlePixels.style.width = `${titlePercent}%`;

    if (titleWidth > titleLimit) {
      barTitlePixels.className = "h-full bg-red-500 rounded-full";
      titleWarnTxt.textContent = "Title exceeds 600px width limit. Google will truncate this tag with ellipses (...).";
      titleWarnTxt.className = "text-[10px] text-red-500 mt-1.5 font-sans font-medium";
      
      // Simulate truncation on UI
      mockTitle.textContent = truncateText(titleVal, 'bold 20px Arial', titleLimit);
    } else {
      barTitlePixels.className = "h-full bg-emerald-500 rounded-full";
      titleWarnTxt.textContent = "Title fits within limits.";
      titleWarnTxt.className = "text-[10px] text-mute mt-1.5 font-sans";
      mockTitle.textContent = titleVal;
    }

    // Description Limits (Desktop: 960px, Mobile: 680px)
    const descLimit = viewMode === 'desktop' ? 960 : 680;
    const descPercent = Math.min(100, (descWidth / descLimit) * 100);
    descPixelsLbl.textContent = `${Math.round(descWidth)}px / ${descLimit}px`;
    barDescPixels.style.width = `${descPercent}%`;

    if (descWidth > descLimit) {
      barDescPixels.className = "h-full bg-red-500 rounded-full";
      descWarnTxt.textContent = `Description exceeds ${descLimit}px limit (${viewMode} standard). Google will truncate it.`;
      descWarnTxt.className = "text-[10px] text-red-500 mt-1.5 font-sans font-medium";
      mockDesc.textContent = truncateText(descVal, '14px Arial', descLimit);
    } else {
      barDescPixels.className = "h-full bg-emerald-500 rounded-full";
      descWarnTxt.textContent = `Description fits within ${viewMode} limits.`;
      descWarnTxt.className = "text-[10px] text-mute mt-1.5 font-sans";
      mockDesc.textContent = descVal;
    }

    // 3. Rich Snippets Simulations
    if (toggleRating.checked) {
      ratingInputs.classList.remove('hidden');
      mockStarsLine.classList.remove('hidden');
      mockStarsVal.textContent = parseFloat(numRating.value).toFixed(1);
      mockStarsVotes.textContent = parseInt(numReviews.value, 10).toLocaleString();
    } else {
      ratingInputs.classList.add('hidden');
      mockStarsLine.classList.add('hidden');
    }

    if (toggleFaq.checked) {
      faqInputs.classList.remove('hidden');
      mockFaqLine.classList.remove('hidden');
      mockFaqQ1.textContent = faqQ1Input.value || "FAQ Question 1";
      mockFaqQ2.textContent = faqQ2Input.value || "FAQ Question 2";
    } else {
      faqInputs.classList.add('hidden');
      mockFaqLine.classList.add('hidden');
    }
  };

  const truncateText = (text: string, fontSpec: string, limit: number) => {
    let current = text;
    if (getPixelWidth(current, fontSpec) <= limit) return current;

    // Binary search/slice truncation
    let low = 0;
    let high = text.length;
    let mid = 0;
    while (low < high) {
      mid = Math.floor((low + high) / 2);
      const test = text.substring(0, mid) + "...";
      if (getPixelWidth(test, fontSpec) > limit) {
        high = mid;
      } else {
        low = mid + 1;
      }
    }
    return text.substring(0, low - 1) + "...";
  };

  const toggleViewMode = (mode: 'desktop' | 'mobile') => {
    viewMode = mode;
    if (mode === 'desktop') {
      btnViewDesktop.classList.add('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold');
      btnViewDesktop.classList.remove('text-mute');
      btnViewMobile.classList.remove('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold');
      btnViewMobile.classList.add('text-mute');
      serpCardContainer.style.maxWidth = "576px"; // Standard Google desktop snippet container
    } else {
      btnViewMobile.classList.add('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold');
      btnViewMobile.classList.remove('text-mute');
      btnViewDesktop.classList.remove('bg-canvas-soft-2', 'text-ink', 'font-semibold');
      btnViewDesktop.classList.add('text-mute');
      serpCardContainer.style.maxWidth = "375px"; // Standard mobile card width
    }
    updateSERP();
  };

  // ============================================================
  // Event Listeners
  // ============================================================
  [titleInput, descInput, urlInput, numRating, numReviews, faqQ1Input, faqQ2Input].forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener('input', updateSERP);
  });

  [toggleRating, toggleFaq].forEach(el => {
    el.addEventListener('change', updateSERP);
  });

  btnViewDesktop.addEventListener('click', () => toggleViewMode('desktop'));
  btnViewMobile.addEventListener('click', () => toggleViewMode('mobile'));

  // Initial Calculation
  updateSERP();
</script>
